WEBVTT

01:25.870 --> 01:34.990
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.340 --> 01:37.880
[Episode 32]

01:40.120 --> 01:40.720
Zhuang,

01:41.180 --> 01:41.840
the shipments are all out.

01:41.840 --> 01:43.100
What are you busy with?

01:43.420 --> 01:44.200
Weren't we hit hard

01:44.200 --> 01:46.000
by counterfeit goods recently?

01:47.090 --> 01:49.890
I'm working on
a new anti-counterfeiting method.

01:52.550 --> 01:53.590
This is a big deal.

01:53.620 --> 01:55.080
You have to get this right.

01:57.890 --> 01:58.620
By the way...

02:02.260 --> 02:03.570
Xu mentioned yesterday

02:03.570 --> 02:05.300
that your grandmother is sick.

02:07.570 --> 02:08.630
Just a small token.

02:08.690 --> 02:09.530
It's not much.

02:09.639 --> 02:10.310
No, no.

02:10.330 --> 02:10.990
No, Zhuang.

02:11.280 --> 02:12.120
I can't take this money.

02:12.120 --> 02:12.630
You and Mr. Xu

02:12.630 --> 02:13.650
are already tight on money.

02:13.650 --> 02:15.510
-I really can't take it.
-Enough.

02:15.540 --> 02:17.070
Her treatment comes first.

02:17.090 --> 02:17.960
If it's not enough,

02:17.960 --> 02:20.090
we'll figure something out together.

02:21.520 --> 02:22.579
Thank you, Zhuang.

02:23.280 --> 02:24.020
Help me watch the shop.

02:24.020 --> 02:25.350
I need to go out for a bit.

03:22.440 --> 03:23.300
Mr. Xu, Zhuang.

03:24.430 --> 03:27.180
What did Chen Guangfa promise you?

03:28.000 --> 03:29.190
Did he say

03:29.270 --> 03:30.590
that after ruining our business,

03:30.590 --> 03:31.590
this place

03:32.110 --> 03:33.640
would be handed over to you?

03:37.840 --> 03:39.090
Mr. Xu, what did you say?

03:39.090 --> 03:40.210
You've got me all wrong.

03:40.210 --> 03:41.670
Then what are you copying?

03:42.410 --> 03:44.190
I...

03:45.690 --> 03:47.280
You still don't know

03:47.300 --> 03:49.700
how your store went out
of business, do you?

03:59.650 --> 04:00.630
[Product Return Form]

04:02.930 --> 04:05.550
[Order Confirmation Receipt]

04:08.290 --> 04:08.810
Isn't this

04:08.810 --> 04:10.670
the batch that got canceled on me?

04:11.460 --> 04:12.800
You already suspected back then

04:12.800 --> 04:14.800
that it was malicious competition.

04:15.100 --> 04:16.760
But you never thought through

04:17.160 --> 04:18.060
why that person

04:18.070 --> 04:18.760
could know

04:18.800 --> 04:21.399
your restock timing
and pricing so precisely.

04:22.300 --> 04:23.650
You mean

04:26.130 --> 04:27.720
the one who ruined me

04:29.690 --> 04:30.850
was Chen Guangfa?

04:31.810 --> 04:33.810
The same way he brought you down back then

04:33.810 --> 04:35.770
is how he plans to take us down now.

04:36.560 --> 04:38.090
You're being used as a pawn.

04:39.280 --> 04:40.140
Mr. Xu, Zhuang,

04:44.010 --> 04:45.900
since when did you know—

04:45.930 --> 04:47.190
That's not important.

04:51.570 --> 04:52.920
If you knew I was trouble,

04:52.920 --> 04:54.180
then why place

04:54.250 --> 04:55.650
that 20,000-unit order?

04:57.330 --> 04:58.530
Those 20,000 units

04:58.550 --> 04:59.920
were

04:59.940 --> 05:01.200
for our Russian friends.

05:01.200 --> 05:02.540
We knew early on

05:02.740 --> 05:04.340
that Chen Guangfa set a trap.

05:04.900 --> 05:06.800
What Chen Guangfa asked you to do

05:07.070 --> 05:08.190
is illegal.

05:08.390 --> 05:09.760
He used you

05:09.780 --> 05:11.290
to keep his own hands clean.

05:11.290 --> 05:12.620
In the end,

05:12.830 --> 05:14.630
you'd be the one taking the fall.

05:15.920 --> 05:17.280
Mr. Xu, Zhuang.

05:18.410 --> 05:19.740
I was really used by him.

05:19.750 --> 05:21.040
Really, believe me.

05:21.070 --> 05:22.480
I was really used by him.

05:23.360 --> 05:24.760
Please forgive me, okay?

05:24.950 --> 05:26.280
I won't dare do it again.

05:34.500 --> 05:34.900
Hello?

05:41.810 --> 05:43.190
Okay, got it.

05:45.060 --> 05:45.640
Just as expected.

05:45.640 --> 05:47.700
The shipment's been held at customs.

05:49.100 --> 05:49.620
Mr. Xu.

05:50.560 --> 05:51.990
Chen Guangfa did this.

05:53.310 --> 05:54.520
What do we do now?

05:54.550 --> 05:56.380
That's 20,000 units.

05:57.250 --> 05:57.980
What now?

05:59.990 --> 06:02.190
There is no customs declaration.

06:03.830 --> 06:07.210
The declared category
is second-hand textiles.

06:07.620 --> 06:08.880
Actually, they are all

06:09.500 --> 06:12.980
newly produced export down jackets.

06:28.920 --> 06:30.180
Xu, you are here.

06:31.630 --> 06:32.010
I heard

06:32.010 --> 06:33.740
one of your shipments got held.

06:33.920 --> 06:35.420
They were about to seize it.

06:35.420 --> 06:36.420
I quickly asked

06:36.450 --> 06:37.480
Mr. Kozlov

06:37.510 --> 06:38.390
to wait for you.

06:38.560 --> 06:39.610
Hurry up and explain yourself.

06:39.610 --> 06:40.810
Is there any misunderstanding?

06:40.810 --> 06:42.140
Then I should thank you.

06:42.360 --> 06:43.490
What a coincidence.

06:43.630 --> 06:44.630
You're here, too.

06:44.720 --> 06:46.650
I'm here to pay additional duties.

06:48.680 --> 06:49.840
As business people,

06:50.070 --> 06:51.470
the most important thing

06:51.810 --> 06:53.470
is that we cannot evade taxes.

06:56.430 --> 06:58.930
Russian Customs Notice No. 12:

06:59.060 --> 07:00.340
Undeclared goods

07:00.370 --> 07:01.910
will be confiscated.

07:02.430 --> 07:03.750
Wait a moment.

07:07.010 --> 07:08.000
Hello.

07:08.300 --> 07:10.200
This is our customs clearance document.

07:10.200 --> 07:11.260
Please take a look.

07:12.370 --> 07:13.020
Okay.

07:13.810 --> 07:15.930
Customs clearance documents
must be checked carefully.

07:15.930 --> 07:17.330
There are too many fakes.

07:21.630 --> 07:22.630
Everything checks out.

07:22.630 --> 07:23.840
These are your goods.

07:23.870 --> 07:24.870
You can take them.

07:24.870 --> 07:26.630
But we don't handle transport.

07:26.770 --> 07:28.750
Don't worry. I'll handle it myself.

07:28.750 --> 07:29.380
Thank you.

07:29.560 --> 07:30.390
Take them?

07:31.330 --> 07:32.510
These are smuggled goods.

07:32.510 --> 07:33.680
And you're letting him take them?

07:33.680 --> 07:34.600
Who told you

07:35.990 --> 07:37.290
my goods are smuggled?

07:42.120 --> 07:43.520
I'd like to file a report.

07:44.630 --> 07:46.150
Guangfa Commerce

07:46.570 --> 07:48.659
has copied MRX brand designs,

07:48.980 --> 07:50.060
is selling counterfeit goods,

07:50.060 --> 07:52.390
and is engaged in large-scale smuggling.

07:57.810 --> 07:59.820
You remind me of an ancient figure—

08:01.060 --> 08:01.770
Lyu Bu.

08:05.690 --> 08:07.020
You're very meticulous

08:07.930 --> 08:08.830
and smart.

08:09.300 --> 08:10.530
But who can prove

08:10.750 --> 08:12.610
which of the goods held at customs

08:12.770 --> 08:13.990
are yours

08:14.390 --> 08:15.520
and which are mine?

08:16.230 --> 08:18.230
You've been to my warehouse, right?

08:18.360 --> 08:19.490
They're identical.

08:21.930 --> 08:23.740
Do you really think your goods

08:24.120 --> 08:26.130
are exactly the same as mine?

08:26.160 --> 08:26.980
What else?

08:27.570 --> 08:29.310
Did you embroider flowers in the pockets?

08:29.310 --> 08:30.020
Indeed.

08:30.570 --> 08:31.130
I admit

08:31.160 --> 08:33.580
that your goods can pass
for the real thing.

08:33.940 --> 08:35.049
But speaking of this,

08:35.049 --> 08:36.120
I have to thank you.

08:39.530 --> 08:41.120
You were the one who said

08:41.140 --> 08:41.870
in business,

08:42.030 --> 08:43.630
you have to cut costs.

08:43.750 --> 08:45.150
A successful businessman

08:45.150 --> 08:47.050
must maximize profits.

08:47.460 --> 08:48.510
And that's exactly

08:48.510 --> 08:49.630
what made me realize

08:49.630 --> 08:50.910
the biggest difference

08:50.910 --> 08:52.780
between us.

08:53.030 --> 08:54.350
Your goods are not bad.

08:54.660 --> 08:55.860
They are top quality.

08:57.030 --> 08:58.360
But the cost is too high.

08:58.490 --> 09:00.930
And there are taxes
and quality inspection procedures.

09:00.930 --> 09:01.550
To put it bluntly,

09:01.550 --> 09:02.550
it's all for show.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.580
Because of that,

09:05.820 --> 09:07.650
your cost has increased by half.

09:08.500 --> 09:09.240
Is it worth it?

09:09.240 --> 09:10.030
In business,

09:10.700 --> 09:12.910
you have to balance the short-term gains

09:12.910 --> 09:14.570
against the long-term value.

09:15.170 --> 09:15.840
Mr. Chen,

09:18.250 --> 09:20.000
why don't you also get

09:20.030 --> 09:21.410
international certification?

09:21.410 --> 09:22.790
Then all the goods outside

09:22.790 --> 09:23.750
will be yours.

09:32.250 --> 09:33.420
Mr. Kozlov,

09:33.590 --> 09:34.980
the serial numbers on this list

09:34.980 --> 09:36.360
match the ones

09:36.360 --> 09:37.160
on our labels.

09:37.160 --> 09:38.290
Feel free to verify.

09:38.860 --> 09:39.370
Indeed.

09:40.100 --> 09:41.740
These formal quality inspections

09:41.740 --> 09:42.890
and customs procedures

09:42.890 --> 09:44.400
increase costs a lot.

09:44.850 --> 09:46.470
But that's exactly why

09:47.530 --> 09:49.230
no matter how hard you scheme,

09:49.260 --> 09:52.230
your fakes will never be real.

09:56.100 --> 09:56.710
All right.

09:57.170 --> 09:58.860
I've accepted your report.

09:59.170 --> 09:59.970
Chen Guangfa,

10:00.080 --> 10:02.150
you can't take your goods away for now.

10:02.150 --> 10:04.950
You must cooperate
with our investigation first.

10:05.460 --> 10:06.590
China-Russia trade

10:06.630 --> 10:08.400
still has a long way to go.

10:08.480 --> 10:08.880
Yes.

10:08.910 --> 10:09.620
We must

10:09.650 --> 10:11.270
strictly inspect such matters

10:11.270 --> 10:12.180
in the future.

10:12.530 --> 10:13.870
We will absolutely not hurt

10:13.870 --> 10:15.670
the feelings of the Chinese friends.

10:15.670 --> 10:16.610
Yes, yes.

10:16.980 --> 10:17.790
Thank you.

10:18.080 --> 10:19.210
Thank you very much.

10:34.500 --> 10:35.620
So this season

10:35.620 --> 10:36.630
comes to

10:36.630 --> 10:37.760
a successful close.

10:38.130 --> 10:39.500
For the new season,

10:39.500 --> 10:41.120
our main focus is to address

10:41.150 --> 10:43.410
everyone's issues with down jackets...

11:05.530 --> 11:07.130
Alright, let's call it a day.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.330
Meeting adjourned.

11:12.860 --> 11:13.980
This house

11:14.080 --> 11:14.840
is yours

11:16.860 --> 11:17.910
now.

11:18.100 --> 11:18.760
Take a look.

11:19.360 --> 11:20.020
Have a seat.

11:23.340 --> 11:25.010
When did you do the paperwork?

11:25.120 --> 11:25.960
This morning.

11:27.740 --> 11:28.740
Didn't you say before

11:27.920 --> 11:31.230
[Building Ownership Certificate
of the People's Republic of China]

11:28.770 --> 11:29.740
you wanted to

11:29.750 --> 11:30.950
renovate this house?

11:31.120 --> 11:32.780
How do you want to renovate it?

11:34.940 --> 11:37.780
I want to divide the bedroom into two.

11:38.630 --> 11:39.340
Agreed.

11:39.890 --> 11:41.510
It'll be easier

11:41.750 --> 11:42.750
when we have a kid.

11:43.790 --> 11:44.620
What I meant was

11:44.620 --> 11:46.480
one bedroom for you and one for me.

11:46.770 --> 11:48.010
You snore so loudly.

11:49.080 --> 11:50.620
Do you dislike me that much?

11:51.650 --> 11:52.850
Give me the house key.

11:52.940 --> 11:53.510
No.

11:53.680 --> 11:54.150
Give it back.

11:54.150 --> 11:54.600
No.

11:54.630 --> 11:55.320
Give me the key back.

11:55.320 --> 11:56.190
No!

11:56.210 --> 11:57.210
Give it back to me.

12:13.260 --> 12:13.820
Aren't we missing

12:13.820 --> 12:15.470
our certificate?

12:15.860 --> 12:16.920
What certificate?

12:16.960 --> 12:18.690
What certificate do you think?

12:21.360 --> 12:22.340
Should we go back to Wenzhou

12:22.340 --> 12:24.070
or Yantai for the certificate?

12:24.440 --> 12:25.500
I'll listen to you.

12:26.000 --> 12:28.640
Okay, then we'll go back tomorrow.

12:29.550 --> 12:31.320
I still have a meeting tomorrow.

12:31.320 --> 12:32.000
A meeting?

12:33.240 --> 12:33.840
Then,

12:34.580 --> 12:36.580
why don't we "have a meeting" first?

12:43.530 --> 12:46.020
[Fortune]

13:53.080 --> 13:54.790
Come on, tourists,

13:54.790 --> 13:55.960
keep up with me.

13:57.720 --> 13:58.840
Just a bit further ahead

13:58.840 --> 14:00.640
and we'll reach the Seine River.

14:01.370 --> 14:02.530
You can take out your cameras now

14:02.530 --> 14:04.390
to snap some photos for memories.

14:05.820 --> 14:07.550
Stay close, don't fall behind.

14:09.170 --> 14:12.030
Look, those pigeons
aren't afraid of people at all.

14:23.280 --> 14:26.710
♪ I heard you sleep alone now ♪

14:27.220 --> 14:30.950
♪ That marriage put you through so much ♪

14:31.760 --> 14:35.380
♪ Hearing that breaks my heart ♪

14:36.420 --> 14:39.510
♪ Makes me want to protect you again ♪

14:40.080 --> 14:43.740
♪ They say you go quiet
when I'm mentioned ♪

14:44.210 --> 14:47.850
♪ Always using alcohol
to sort out right and wrong ♪

14:48.330 --> 14:52.440
♪ I don't understand
how deep your love runs ♪

14:52.780 --> 14:56.620
♪ And you don't understand
how much I miss you ♪

14:56.200 --> 14:58.520
[Name: Tao Liangliang]

14:58.980 --> 15:03.120
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

15:04.290 --> 15:07.970
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

15:09.280 --> 15:13.330
♪ There's too much
in this world left unresolved ♪

15:13.930 --> 15:17.440
♪ You're the arrow
that pierces through my longing ♪

15:17.950 --> 15:22.050
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

15:23.240 --> 15:26.900
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

15:23.270 --> 15:24.020
Buddy,

15:24.460 --> 15:25.450
are you okay?

15:28.590 --> 15:32.550
♪ Looking back on those years
we held each other up ♪

15:30.370 --> 15:32.290
Hello.

15:33.150 --> 15:37.520
♪ When we loved recklessly,
no matter the cost ♪

15:38.770 --> 15:42.850
♪ Sometimes I wonder, in this world ♪

15:38.930 --> 15:42.290
[Ambulance]

15:43.520 --> 15:46.730
♪ Are there other versions of me ♪

15:47.320 --> 15:51.300
♪ Still foolishly clinging to love ♪

15:50.620 --> 15:52.230
Excuse me.

15:51.820 --> 15:55.370
♪ Clinging to other versions of you ♪

15:52.360 --> 15:54.290
Have you seen this person?

15:55.880 --> 15:59.540
♪ If somewhere out there ♪

15:57.000 --> 15:58.310
Hurry up.

16:00.000 --> 16:03.670
♪ Other versions of us exist ♪

16:04.120 --> 16:08.350
♪ I truly hope their story ♪

16:08.750 --> 16:13.470
♪ Gets a happy ending ♪

16:14.950 --> 16:18.970
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

16:20.130 --> 16:23.710
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

16:23.250 --> 16:25.100
You can check it out over there.

16:25.120 --> 16:25.970
Thank you.

16:25.380 --> 16:29.320
♪ There's too much
in this world left unresolved ♪

16:30.110 --> 16:33.590
♪ You're the arrow
that pierces through my longing ♪

16:34.030 --> 16:37.970
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

16:39.290 --> 16:42.860
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

16:44.550 --> 16:47.970
♪ Looking back on those years
we held each other up ♪

16:48.860 --> 16:53.330
♪ When we loved recklessly,
no matter the cost ♪

17:19.849 --> 17:20.380
Hello?

17:22.010 --> 17:22.980
Hello, Ma'am.

17:23.530 --> 17:26.440
This is
the Paris 7th District Police Station.

17:26.750 --> 17:28.800
Are you Shen Ranran?

17:29.770 --> 17:32.850
We found a deceased Asian male,

17:33.700 --> 17:37.140
Mr. Tao Liangliang,

17:37.310 --> 17:40.160
at Les Invalides Square.

17:40.880 --> 17:42.160
When he was found,

17:42.400 --> 17:44.330
he had already stopped breathing.

17:44.810 --> 17:46.030
We found your contact information

17:46.030 --> 17:47.380
in his pocket.

17:47.640 --> 17:49.650
If you are a relative,

17:49.750 --> 17:51.530
please come to assist
with the investigation

17:51.530 --> 17:55.460
and handle his affairs within 48 hours.

19:39.750 --> 19:42.420
How did you end up getting this disease?

19:51.460 --> 19:54.160
Wishing Liangliang and Ranran

19:54.250 --> 19:56.920
a happy marriage!

20:05.940 --> 20:06.420
Ranran.

20:07.700 --> 20:09.030
In any place

20:09.120 --> 20:10.330
and in every way,

20:11.400 --> 20:12.800
I will love you forever.

20:16.940 --> 20:17.800
In the future,

20:17.850 --> 20:19.780
if anything goes down in Sijiu City

20:19.790 --> 20:21.710
within my power,

20:21.810 --> 20:23.100
just let me know.

20:31.550 --> 20:33.480
No one stands forever in this world.

20:33.480 --> 20:34.750
My name is Liangliang—

20:34.980 --> 20:36.110
don't you forget it.

21:40.550 --> 21:41.810
Hello, Director Weng.

21:41.810 --> 21:43.210
How have you been lately?

21:43.550 --> 21:44.380
Xu.

21:45.480 --> 21:46.610
I'm doing very well.

21:47.050 --> 21:48.560
I'm in Chengdu now.

21:48.680 --> 21:50.220
The filming is about to start.

21:50.220 --> 21:51.950
What are you filming this time?

21:52.720 --> 21:56.240
"The Late Love"
has finally started filming.

21:57.960 --> 21:58.920
"The Late Love?"

21:58.940 --> 21:59.500
Yes.

21:59.980 --> 22:00.640
You're going to shoot it?

22:00.640 --> 22:01.140
That's right.

22:01.140 --> 22:02.240
Well, this is real?

22:03.030 --> 22:03.550
Hey, Director Weng,

22:03.550 --> 22:04.780
what's going on?

22:04.850 --> 22:05.460
It's so sudden.

22:05.460 --> 22:06.720
I'm totally confused.

22:07.090 --> 22:08.290
Hey, didn't the studio

22:08.290 --> 22:10.290
have a lot of issues with the script?

22:11.220 --> 22:11.960
Yes,

22:13.440 --> 22:14.730
so I have to mention

22:15.440 --> 22:17.880
your master, Mr. He.

22:18.850 --> 22:20.290
He did a lot of work

22:20.850 --> 22:22.870
for this film.

22:27.830 --> 22:28.510
Hello.

22:29.380 --> 22:30.180
Director Gao.

22:31.200 --> 22:32.190
I am He Sheng.

22:33.510 --> 22:34.480
I heard

22:34.940 --> 22:36.420
the studio is collecting

22:36.510 --> 22:37.980
good original scripts.

22:38.790 --> 22:41.000
I would like to recommend

22:41.960 --> 22:43.020
the one

22:43.170 --> 22:46.110
my apprentice and I wrote five years ago—

22:46.610 --> 22:47.770
"The Late Love."

22:50.640 --> 22:51.570
This is

22:51.710 --> 22:53.300
my last script.

22:55.090 --> 22:58.910
I won't be writing
any more scripts from here on out.

23:02.750 --> 23:04.870
If you have any suggestions,

23:06.320 --> 23:08.400
I'll revise accordingly.

23:09.780 --> 23:11.410
I'll go through it word by word,

23:11.410 --> 23:13.470
even down to every punctuation mark.

23:15.060 --> 23:16.370
I really want

23:17.090 --> 23:18.360
it to be filmed.

23:27.400 --> 23:33.840
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

23:32.640 --> 23:33.550
Xu Shengli.

23:34.140 --> 23:35.050
I've seen it.

23:35.850 --> 23:39.600
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

23:37.090 --> 23:37.690
Come here.

23:37.740 --> 23:38.800
Let's take a photo.

23:39.240 --> 23:40.040
Go over there.

23:45.440 --> 23:47.470
Ready. 1, 2, 3.

23:49.330 --> 23:49.870
Done.

23:49.900 --> 23:51.160
Let's take one together.

23:51.160 --> 23:51.690
Okay.

23:51.880 --> 23:53.120
Let me find someone to help us.

23:53.120 --> 23:53.850
Hello.

23:54.200 --> 23:55.580
Could you help us take a photo?

23:55.580 --> 23:57.120
-Okay.
-Thank you.

24:00.770 --> 24:02.290
Hey, look at the camera.

24:02.590 --> 24:04.420
1, 2, 3.

24:05.030 --> 24:06.230
["The Late Love"—Now Showing
in Theaters Nationwide]

24:13.330 --> 24:14.180
This group of characters

24:14.180 --> 24:15.440
has been through so much.

24:15.440 --> 24:16.980
Shouldn't this farewell

24:17.500 --> 24:19.030
feel a bit more meaningful?

24:19.500 --> 24:21.030
That's not refined enough.

24:21.090 --> 24:22.290
Think about it again.

24:23.600 --> 24:24.710
God

24:25.090 --> 24:27.260
is the cruelest screenwriter of all.

24:29.310 --> 24:33.110
This is a script written

24:33.330 --> 24:35.720
by Xu Shengli and me together.

24:36.510 --> 24:37.840
It's as good as it gets.

24:39.920 --> 24:42.280
Slow down. Slow down.

24:42.530 --> 24:44.420
Slow down.

24:53.770 --> 24:56.680
From now on, we will

24:56.960 --> 24:58.590
go our separate ways.

24:59.880 --> 25:00.830
In this world,

25:01.680 --> 25:06.090
a lot of things just can't be avoided.

25:08.570 --> 25:10.320
What we can do

25:11.310 --> 25:12.110
is

25:13.680 --> 25:16.090
protect what we want,

25:17.960 --> 25:20.570
carry what we're meant to carry,

25:22.460 --> 25:26.190
and keep moving forward.

25:30.550 --> 25:35.050
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]
[Director: Weng Xingguo]

25:36.190 --> 25:40.920
[This film is dedicated to the memory
of Mr. He Sheng]

26:16.790 --> 26:23.080
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

26:25.550 --> 26:26.010
Cut.

26:28.700 --> 26:29.830
Good job, everyone.

26:29.940 --> 26:30.510
That's a wrap.

26:30.510 --> 26:31.570
Thanks, Director Cui.

26:31.570 --> 26:32.610
Come, let's take a group photo.

26:32.610 --> 26:33.990
Come, everyone, come.

26:34.330 --> 26:36.970
Happy wrap!

27:05.440 --> 27:09.610
[Hostel]

27:08.790 --> 27:09.730
Northeasterner. Happy New Year.

27:09.730 --> 27:10.380
Happy New Year.

27:10.380 --> 27:11.710
You're so hardworking.

27:14.010 --> 27:15.150
Let me plug it in and see.

27:15.150 --> 27:17.030
[Hostel]

27:15.450 --> 27:16.710
Let me check on my girl.

27:17.170 --> 27:18.430
She sleeps so soundly.

27:18.790 --> 27:20.010
Let's go back to the room. Hurry.

27:20.010 --> 27:23.120
[Hostel]

27:21.780 --> 27:22.370
Let's go.

27:23.620 --> 27:28.210
[Hostel]

27:38.720 --> 27:41.990
[2018]

27:43.250 --> 27:44.110
In the end,

27:44.110 --> 27:45.070
it's all the same no matter
who you're with.

27:45.070 --> 27:46.740
There you go again,
making a big deal out of everything.

27:46.740 --> 27:47.850
Hey, have you ever stepped in

27:47.850 --> 27:50.140
when your son got into conflicts
with others?

27:50.140 --> 27:51.310
I'm the one handling everything.

27:51.310 --> 27:52.400
while you're the one playing the good guy.

27:52.400 --> 27:54.060
Did I say I wouldn't handle it?

27:54.530 --> 27:55.990
Don't I need to make money?

27:57.550 --> 27:58.480
You sit here every day,

27:58.480 --> 28:00.200
pretending you're working.

28:00.430 --> 28:02.360
How many times
have you been to our kids' school?

28:02.360 --> 28:04.740
How many parent-teacher conferences
have you attended?

28:04.740 --> 28:05.660
Big things, small things—

28:05.660 --> 28:06.660
I manage them all.

28:07.980 --> 28:08.810
If it works, we stay.

28:08.810 --> 28:09.740
If not, we split.

28:13.810 --> 28:15.300
Honey, don't be angry.

28:15.330 --> 28:16.590
Don't be angry.

28:16.740 --> 28:17.840
You just

28:18.050 --> 28:19.580
said what you really think.

28:21.460 --> 28:22.010
Look,

28:22.140 --> 28:23.820
are those lines even in the script?

28:23.820 --> 28:25.350
Isn't it written like that?

28:27.500 --> 28:28.800
Alright.

28:29.270 --> 28:31.200
You don't need to run lines with me.

28:31.400 --> 28:32.930
You're too into character.

28:35.000 --> 28:37.070
I was kind enough to help you run lines.

28:37.070 --> 28:38.270
You've got no conscience.

28:38.270 --> 28:39.280
I will keep

28:39.310 --> 28:41.380
your great kindness in mind.

28:48.250 --> 28:49.580
But then again,

28:49.920 --> 28:50.980
you're actually quite suited

28:50.980 --> 28:52.310
to write family dramas.

28:53.090 --> 28:56.090
Just listening to couples talk
like this is annoying.

28:56.110 --> 28:57.730
Art comes from life.

28:57.940 --> 28:59.270
Mr. He said

28:59.440 --> 29:01.170
-Comes from what?
-if you want—

29:02.180 --> 29:03.240
It comes from life,

29:04.070 --> 29:05.800
but it must be higher than life.

29:06.550 --> 29:08.570
You must fully use your imagination

29:08.680 --> 29:10.470
to shape it into art.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.240
Which parts are crafted,

29:12.240 --> 29:13.900
and which come from real life?

29:14.270 --> 29:14.900
This...

29:15.500 --> 29:16.560
this script of mine

29:16.560 --> 29:18.330
d-doesn't come from real life.

29:18.570 --> 29:19.900
It's all fictionalized.

29:19.900 --> 29:21.630
It... It's all fictionalized.

29:27.270 --> 29:28.920
Your pen is so old.

29:29.440 --> 29:30.480
I'll get you a new one later.

29:30.480 --> 29:31.810
No need, I like this one.

29:43.680 --> 29:45.240
But isn't  your script

29:46.510 --> 29:47.720
too pessimistic?

29:47.850 --> 29:49.190
Isn't it good

29:49.320 --> 29:50.050
living an ordinary life

29:50.050 --> 29:51.110
like the two of us?

29:55.770 --> 29:57.760
Being able to live an ordinary life

29:58.850 --> 30:00.160
is already very lucky.

30:01.550 --> 30:03.220
Life is full of trivial,

30:03.250 --> 30:04.400
messy details,

30:05.250 --> 30:07.910
but that doesn't mean
there's no real love in it.

30:08.660 --> 30:11.670
People make different choices,

30:12.070 --> 30:13.730
so their fates are different.

30:14.920 --> 30:15.910
To be honest,

30:17.110 --> 30:18.910
having lived for most of my life,

30:21.200 --> 30:22.200
I'm very content.

30:25.250 --> 30:26.140
You're right.

30:28.980 --> 30:32.650
There's more than one standard answer
to happiness.

30:37.350 --> 30:38.440
Right now,

30:39.720 --> 30:40.810
I just hope our parents

30:40.810 --> 30:41.750
stay healthy,

30:42.900 --> 30:44.440
and Dongdong and Chunchun

30:44.790 --> 30:45.810
grow up well.

30:47.180 --> 30:48.580
That's all that matters.

30:50.270 --> 30:50.750
Right.

30:53.570 --> 30:54.870
The most important thing is that you

30:54.870 --> 30:55.970
don't make me mad.

30:58.350 --> 31:00.660
When it comes to me,
I'm the one making you mad.

31:00.660 --> 31:01.740
I make you mad.

31:03.140 --> 31:03.810
Okay.

31:05.720 --> 31:08.290
Chunchun, give me back
my roasted fish fillets!

31:08.290 --> 31:09.640
Give them back!

31:09.720 --> 31:11.850
Chunchun, give them back to me.

31:11.920 --> 31:12.540
Listen.

31:12.570 --> 31:13.510
They're fighting again.

31:13.510 --> 31:14.430
Don't fight!

31:14.610 --> 31:16.540
Grandpa, look at him.

31:17.030 --> 31:18.300
What's going on?

31:18.500 --> 31:20.700
Chunchun took my roasted fish fillets.

31:20.830 --> 31:21.430
Is that so?

31:22.800 --> 31:23.720
As an older brother,

31:23.720 --> 31:25.740
you should give in to your little sister.

31:25.740 --> 31:27.230
She's already eaten a lot.

31:27.310 --> 31:28.740
There's only one bag left.

31:28.740 --> 31:29.600
Only one bag?

31:29.640 --> 31:30.760
That's impossible.

31:30.760 --> 31:31.400
Go.

31:31.530 --> 31:33.330
-Go ask your dad for them.
-It's not like we don't have more at home.

31:33.330 --> 31:34.270
Go ask your dad for them.

31:34.270 --> 31:35.180
Go. Go.

31:35.270 --> 31:36.270
No more fighting.

31:37.810 --> 31:38.530
These kids

31:38.590 --> 31:39.400
are exactly like Shengli

31:39.400 --> 31:40.460
when he was little.

31:43.000 --> 31:43.860
Dad,

31:44.240 --> 31:45.900
are there any roasted fish fillets left?

31:45.900 --> 31:46.410
Yes,

31:46.440 --> 31:47.400
they're in the drawer under

31:47.400 --> 31:48.860
the TV cabinet.

31:48.980 --> 31:50.700
Dad, give them to me first.

31:50.790 --> 31:52.330
Grandpa sent me.

31:52.610 --> 31:54.400
You're not a little kid anymore.

31:54.400 --> 31:55.460
Get them yourself.

31:59.690 --> 32:00.320
Look,

32:01.500 --> 32:03.550
every time they come,
the first thing they do is call for Dad.

32:03.550 --> 32:04.720
And you still said
I don't care about them.

32:04.720 --> 32:05.980
How else should I care?

32:10.680 --> 32:11.240
[Shichahai]

32:19.590 --> 32:20.780
Is this still the old

32:20.810 --> 32:22.210
Shichahai private room?

32:22.220 --> 32:22.940
It's still the original

32:22.940 --> 32:24.180
Shichahai private room.

32:24.180 --> 32:24.790
It's just that

32:24.790 --> 32:25.960
we knocked through

32:26.010 --> 32:26.600
the adjacent rooms.

32:26.600 --> 32:27.550
This way, your dining experience

32:27.550 --> 32:28.750
will feel more spacious and comfortable,

32:28.750 --> 32:29.280
won't it?

32:32.380 --> 32:33.110
Pretty good.

32:33.790 --> 32:34.410
Mr. Xu,

32:34.440 --> 32:36.290
not only has our hotel
been recently renovated,

32:36.290 --> 32:36.980
but we have also

32:36.980 --> 32:38.580
introduced many new dishes.

32:38.590 --> 32:41.110
We have "Abundant Wealth",
"Rolling in Money",

32:41.110 --> 32:42.700
"Happy Marriage", "Pure and Clear",

32:42.700 --> 32:44.900
"Rising High," and "Flying Together."

32:45.610 --> 32:47.410
I want to eat Beijing roast duck,

32:47.900 --> 32:49.500
braised pork balls in gravy,

32:49.810 --> 32:52.510
shredded pork with sweet bean sauce,
braised pork joint,

32:52.510 --> 32:54.900
braised mutton strips, quick-boiled tripe,

32:54.900 --> 32:57.450
and old Beijing noodles
with soybean paste.

32:57.830 --> 32:58.410
Sir,

32:58.440 --> 32:59.940
the dishes I just mentioned

32:59.940 --> 33:00.790
are exactly

33:00.830 --> 33:02.110
the classic Beijing dishes you asked for.

33:02.110 --> 33:03.350
We just changed the names.

33:03.350 --> 33:04.460
Just keeping up with the times.

33:04.460 --> 33:05.920
We just changed the names.

33:06.090 --> 33:08.110
Okay, as long as you have them.

33:09.750 --> 33:10.610
So we're still booking lunch

33:10.610 --> 33:11.940
for tomorrow, right?

33:13.640 --> 33:14.200
Right.

33:14.960 --> 33:17.770
Our people will all be here tomorrow.

33:22.050 --> 33:24.110
Mr. Guo, have something to eat first.

33:26.720 --> 33:29.290
Is this your first day at work?

33:30.660 --> 33:32.270
When have I ever eaten stuff like this?

33:32.270 --> 33:33.460
Isn't it a waste?

33:35.830 --> 33:36.610
I'll eat it.

33:38.700 --> 33:40.360
Xiaobao is really something.

33:40.720 --> 33:42.520
He even got himself a secretary.

33:44.070 --> 33:44.730
Drink this.

33:46.740 --> 33:47.800
Thank you, Mr. Guo.

33:55.500 --> 33:56.500
Have some of this.

34:01.660 --> 34:02.690
Hello.

34:02.790 --> 34:05.610
Pizza, rice, or a hamburger?

34:05.720 --> 34:06.740
Rice.

34:06.810 --> 34:07.680
Rice.

34:07.850 --> 34:08.420
Okay.

34:12.920 --> 34:13.719
Hello, ma'am.

34:14.110 --> 34:15.710
What would you like to order?

34:18.940 --> 34:20.230
[Steak]

34:18.980 --> 34:19.510
This one.

34:20.050 --> 34:20.500
Then, how would you like

34:20.500 --> 34:22.040
your steak cooked?

34:23.170 --> 34:23.830
Well done.

34:25.260 --> 34:26.000
Are you sure?

34:29.980 --> 34:30.780
Are you trying to be difficult?

34:30.780 --> 34:32.179
I want it well-done.

34:32.550 --> 34:33.650
Give me a well-done one.

34:33.650 --> 34:34.530
Heat it up right now.

34:34.530 --> 34:35.130
Remake it.

34:36.710 --> 34:37.150
Yes.

34:38.000 --> 34:38.460
Okay.

35:01.090 --> 35:01.970
Honey.

35:02.920 --> 35:03.920
Did I scare you?

35:04.170 --> 35:05.330
Wait inside.

35:05.420 --> 35:06.020
It's fine.

35:06.230 --> 35:06.920
Hey, it's not fine.

35:06.920 --> 35:08.260
You've been waiting forever.

35:08.260 --> 35:09.340
And you're wearing high heels.

35:09.340 --> 35:10.800
You'll be exhausted soon.

35:10.940 --> 35:12.340
I want to wait right here.

35:15.010 --> 35:17.380
Alright, then I'll wait with you.

35:18.690 --> 35:19.260
Okay.

35:29.940 --> 35:31.510
Zhuang, Mr. Xu.

35:37.850 --> 35:38.460
In the blink of an eye,

35:38.460 --> 35:39.890
over a decade has passed.

35:42.670 --> 35:44.240
You haven't changed a bit.

35:45.280 --> 35:46.540
You've gotten so thin.

35:46.870 --> 35:49.330
He hasn't been giving you
a hard time, has he?

35:49.440 --> 35:50.550
Come on, after all these years,

35:50.550 --> 35:52.050
neither of you has changed.

35:52.050 --> 35:54.050
You both are still pretty and young.

35:55.250 --> 35:55.800
Ranran.

35:55.800 --> 35:57.110
Are you leaving again this time?

35:57.110 --> 35:57.900
Now that I'm back,

35:57.900 --> 35:59.360
I'll stay and work in Beijing,

35:59.360 --> 36:00.610
so I can take care of the elders.

36:00.610 --> 36:01.850
That's wonderful.

36:02.480 --> 36:02.940
Then...

36:03.300 --> 36:05.030
Then, we can see each other often.

36:05.030 --> 36:05.990
Of course.

36:06.190 --> 36:06.820
In that case,

36:06.820 --> 36:08.460
you two can see each other every day.

36:08.460 --> 36:09.860
You two can even live together.

36:09.860 --> 36:11.080
Don't be jealous.

36:11.110 --> 36:13.030
I won't be jealous. Me, jealous?

36:13.400 --> 36:15.410
The great screenwriter and big star—

36:15.410 --> 36:16.340
You're all here?

36:16.710 --> 36:18.230
Little Northeasterner, the big boss.

36:18.230 --> 36:19.550
A small boss. A small boss.

36:19.550 --> 36:20.480
Long time no see.

36:20.480 --> 36:21.340
Long time no see.

36:21.340 --> 36:22.500
Big star?

36:22.610 --> 36:24.050
I changed careers a long time ago.

36:24.050 --> 36:24.840
You will always be

36:24.840 --> 36:26.440
the big star of Seasons Change Hostel.

36:26.440 --> 36:27.200
In my heart,

36:27.230 --> 36:28.340
none of the current stars

36:28.340 --> 36:29.500
can compare to you.

36:29.880 --> 36:30.660
I heard

36:30.680 --> 36:31.840
you've turned Seasons Change Hostel

36:31.840 --> 36:32.980
into a big hotel.

36:33.730 --> 36:34.670
I opened a new place.

36:34.670 --> 36:35.960
It's just a small hotel.

36:35.960 --> 36:37.670
What about
the original Seasons Change Hostel?

36:37.670 --> 36:38.410
The new place

36:38.440 --> 36:40.120
is managed by our chairman.

36:40.300 --> 36:40.830
As for me,

36:40.840 --> 36:41.950
if I have time,

36:41.980 --> 36:43.070
I still like staying

36:43.070 --> 36:44.930
at our old Seasons Change Hostel.

36:45.130 --> 36:45.690
Yeah.

36:46.510 --> 36:47.600
That's our roots.

36:47.760 --> 36:49.340
Without Seasons Change Hostel,

36:49.340 --> 36:50.820
we wouldn't be who we are today.

36:50.820 --> 36:51.280
Yes.

36:52.670 --> 36:53.870
For the meal today,

36:53.960 --> 36:55.380
Little Northeasterner
should take the seat of honor.

36:55.380 --> 36:56.500
How can I take the seat of honor?

36:56.500 --> 36:57.320
I'm so young.

36:57.530 --> 36:58.690
What do you mean, young?

36:58.690 --> 37:00.380
You must take the seat of honor.
You're paying.

37:00.380 --> 37:02.460
Sure, I can pay.

37:02.530 --> 37:03.280
But let me tell you,

37:03.280 --> 37:04.320
you're always welcome

37:04.320 --> 37:05.820
to stay at our hotel anytime.

37:05.820 --> 37:06.380
Okay then.

37:06.380 --> 37:07.230
When we go,

37:07.260 --> 37:08.960
we'll still just give him six yuan.

37:08.960 --> 37:10.250
I'm fine with that.

37:10.280 --> 37:10.720
Chairman.

37:10.720 --> 37:12.030
-Is that Okay?
-Is that Okay? 6 yuan.

37:12.030 --> 37:13.030
I'll listen to you.

37:13.030 --> 37:14.160
Thanks for the face.

37:14.800 --> 37:16.100
It's a deal then.

37:16.210 --> 37:17.790
6 yuan per bed.

37:17.940 --> 37:19.010
I'll sell

37:19.050 --> 37:19.690
my house

37:19.690 --> 37:21.750
and move into Seasons Change Hostel.

37:23.130 --> 37:25.090
Shengli.

37:25.360 --> 37:25.890
Zongbao.

37:25.990 --> 37:26.840
Zhuang Zhuang.

37:26.840 --> 37:28.300
You haven't changed a bit.

37:28.300 --> 37:29.300
And I'm here, too.

37:29.300 --> 37:30.000
Ranran.

37:30.130 --> 37:31.230
How are you? Good?

37:31.280 --> 37:31.940
Good, good.

37:33.690 --> 37:34.630
Zongbao.

37:34.650 --> 37:36.090
You've moved to Beijing.

37:36.130 --> 37:37.750
Why are you so late?

37:38.480 --> 37:39.970
I was halfway here

37:40.000 --> 37:41.860
when I realized I forgot this corn juice.

37:41.860 --> 37:43.150
So I went back to get it.

37:43.650 --> 37:45.310
It's this year's new product.

37:45.940 --> 37:46.800
Have a taste.

37:47.030 --> 37:48.160
See if it's any good.

37:48.920 --> 37:50.440
You changed the packaging.

37:50.440 --> 37:52.170
I have to keep up with the times.

37:53.360 --> 37:54.670
Everyone is here.

37:54.670 --> 37:56.140
Which room are we in?

37:56.840 --> 37:58.160
Still Shichahai.

38:01.090 --> 38:02.410
[Shichahai]

38:05.820 --> 38:09.030
Let's not fight today.

38:10.840 --> 38:12.500
We are too old to fight.

38:12.760 --> 38:14.170
Alright, everyone's hungry.

38:14.170 --> 38:15.170
Let's go in.

38:15.460 --> 38:16.500
Let's go.

38:16.590 --> 38:17.140
Go inside

38:17.610 --> 38:18.610
and eat together.

38:19.110 --> 38:23.150
[Shichahai]

38:19.730 --> 38:20.500
After lunch,

38:20.520 --> 38:23.050
let's go check out
the Seasons Change Hostel.

38:29.850 --> 38:32.310
Luogu Hutong has really changed,
hasn't it?

38:32.610 --> 38:34.200
Lin's bun shop

38:34.300 --> 38:35.110
Bun Shop.

38:35.280 --> 38:36.740
is now run by his daughter.

38:37.770 --> 38:38.880
They have several locations now.

38:38.880 --> 38:39.480
They even opened a branch over there.

38:39.480 --> 38:39.960
We used to

38:39.960 --> 38:41.160
always eat buns here.

38:43.070 --> 38:43.630
How about

38:43.650 --> 38:45.360
going check out the new hotel?

38:45.530 --> 38:46.890
Let's go and take a look.

38:47.020 --> 38:48.820
Let's head back to the hostel first.

38:48.820 --> 38:49.750
-I agree.
-Okay.

38:50.090 --> 38:50.800
I also want to see

38:50.800 --> 38:51.860
what Seasons Change Hostel

38:51.860 --> 38:53.090
looks like now.

38:53.580 --> 38:54.700
I have to say.

38:54.800 --> 38:55.680
This whole vibe

38:55.710 --> 38:57.190
really takes me back

38:57.780 --> 39:00.050
to those days when we were all wasted,

39:00.300 --> 39:01.630
stumbling our way

39:01.630 --> 39:03.610
toward Seasons Change Hostel together.

39:03.610 --> 39:04.730
Right now,

39:04.760 --> 39:06.670
we are like a senior tour group

39:06.780 --> 39:07.980
visiting the hutong.

39:08.050 --> 39:09.400
What do you mean, senior?

39:09.400 --> 39:10.420
You are the senior here.

39:10.420 --> 39:11.280
I'll take a picture of

39:11.280 --> 39:12.070
that white hair of yours.

39:12.070 --> 39:14.590
-The tour group is missing something.
-Let me take a photo.

39:14.590 --> 39:15.380
A tour guide.

39:15.960 --> 39:17.390
Are you hinting at me?

39:17.530 --> 39:19.370
Yes, let's see what you can do.

39:19.670 --> 39:22.330
Do you still remember your lines
from back then?

39:22.380 --> 39:24.050
I can remember them even in my sleep.

39:24.050 --> 39:24.670
Alright, alright.

39:24.670 --> 39:25.930
I-I'm recording this.

39:25.940 --> 39:27.470
Come on, you say it.

39:28.360 --> 39:30.490
Come on, senior tour group, follow me.

39:30.610 --> 39:31.630
What senior tour group?

39:31.630 --> 39:33.210
North, south, all around.

39:33.630 --> 39:35.340
Visiting kin, visiting friends.

39:35.340 --> 39:36.550
On business, on vacation.

39:36.550 --> 39:37.980
-Chasing fortune or chasing dreams—
-It's the same line.

39:37.980 --> 39:38.840
-It's exactly the same.
-We

39:38.840 --> 39:39.260
Right.

39:39.650 --> 39:41.110
come from all corners of the country.

39:41.110 --> 39:42.360
At Seasons Change Hostel,

39:42.360 --> 39:43.440
we are one family.

39:43.730 --> 39:46.380
Seasons Change Hostel
helps your dreams come true.

39:46.380 --> 39:47.340
Are those the words?

39:47.340 --> 39:48.440
Yes.

39:51.030 --> 39:52.760
Come on, stay close, everyone.

39:53.900 --> 39:55.500
It hasn't changed much here.

39:56.670 --> 39:57.930
Come on, let's go home.

39:58.000 --> 39:58.860
We're home!

40:06.720 --> 40:10.640
[Seasons Change Hostel]

40:11.880 --> 40:13.090
Hurry up, come on.

40:21.630 --> 40:22.630
Northeasterner.

40:22.760 --> 40:24.460
W-What are you doing?

40:29.000 --> 40:31.590
I hurried here. I'm not late, am I?

40:39.890 --> 40:40.990
I'm back.

40:43.170 --> 40:44.350
Is everyone here?

40:44.420 --> 40:44.950
Hurry up.

40:52.500 --> 40:53.380
I'm coming.

40:55.670 --> 40:57.270
You're taking a group photo?

40:57.490 --> 40:59.020
[Seasons Change Hostel]

40:57.710 --> 40:58.280
Come on.

41:04.550 --> 41:05.570
The camera is really expensive.

41:05.570 --> 41:06.320
Cao?

41:06.710 --> 41:08.060
I'm late. I'm late.

41:07.760 --> 41:09.680
[Seasons Change Hostel]

41:09.650 --> 41:10.550
I took a detour.

41:12.530 --> 41:13.340
Should I

41:13.120 --> 41:16.570
[Seasons Change Hostel]

41:13.340 --> 41:14.890
change clothes today?

41:15.010 --> 41:16.390
You look very sharp.

41:17.070 --> 41:17.500
Isn't this your

41:17.500 --> 41:18.210
best-looking outfit?

41:18.210 --> 41:19.260
Uncle Guo looks the best.

41:19.260 --> 41:19.860
Nonsense.

41:19.960 --> 41:20.960
Is everything ready?

41:20.960 --> 41:21.980
-Come on.
-We're ready.

41:21.980 --> 41:22.440
Come on.

41:22.510 --> 41:23.510
Let's begin then.

41:24.800 --> 41:26.570
You took a photo without me?

41:32.550 --> 41:38.230
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

41:38.720 --> 41:44.550
♪ And never brought to mind? ♪

41:45.090 --> 41:50.770
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

41:51.160 --> 41:56.800
♪ And auld lang syne? ♪

41:51.280 --> 41:52.880
-Liangliang?
-Liangliang.

41:55.070 --> 41:55.960
Come here.

41:57.440 --> 41:59.070
Liangliang.

41:57.730 --> 42:03.490
♪ We twa hae run about the braes ♪

41:59.400 --> 42:01.150
You are here?

42:01.870 --> 42:02.980
I kind of missed you today.

42:02.980 --> 42:03.920
Don't know why.

42:03.930 --> 42:09.020
♪ And pou'd the gowans fine ♪

42:04.360 --> 42:05.350
Hurry up.

42:05.380 --> 42:07.000
We have to go eat noodles after this.

42:07.000 --> 42:07.800
Liang.

42:08.300 --> 42:10.190
Mr. Tao, stop putting on airs.

42:10.210 --> 42:11.230
Hurry up. We're waiting for you.

42:10.240 --> 42:16.150
♪ But we've wander'd monie a weary fit ♪

42:11.300 --> 42:11.670
Come on

42:11.670 --> 42:13.030
-Come on.
-Hurry.

42:11.850 --> 42:15.630
[Seasons Change Hostel]

42:16.530 --> 42:21.890
♪ Sin' auld lang syne ♪

42:24.660 --> 42:30.320
♪ For auld lang syne, my dear ♪

42:27.550 --> 42:28.750
5-second countdown.

42:29.400 --> 42:30.050
5.

42:30.390 --> 42:33.850
[Seasons Change Hostel]

42:30.860 --> 42:31.510
4.

42:30.950 --> 42:36.890
♪ For auld lang syne ♪

42:31.980 --> 42:32.630
3.

42:33.260 --> 42:33.920
2.

42:34.880 --> 42:35.530
1.

42:35.900 --> 42:38.780
Seasons Change Hostel!

42:36.010 --> 42:39.010
[Seasons Change Hostel]

42:37.300 --> 42:43.150
♪ We'll tak a cup o' kindness yet ♪

42:43.580 --> 42:49.250
♪ For auld lang syne ♪
